<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName LSID="779F11C3FA33521CA77BAA085CE562DD" authority="M. E. Barr et al., Mycotaxon 29: 196. 1987." class="Dothideomycetes" family="Shiraiaceae" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Grandigallia M.E. Barr et al., Mycotaxon 29: 196. 1987.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
See 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" author="Ariyawansa, HA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="35 - 47" refId="B2" refString="Ariyawansa, HA, Kang, JC, Alias, SA, Chukeatirote, E, Hyde, KD, 2013. Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis). . Phytotaxa 147: 35 - 47" title="Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" volume="147" year="2013">Ariyawansa et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia dictyospora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dictyospora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia dictyospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
M.E. Barr et al., Mycotaxon 29: 196 (1987)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by Barr (1987) and is typified by 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. dictyospora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dictyospora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G. dictyospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The fungus infects branches of 
<taxonomicName class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Polylepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polylepis sericea" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polylepis sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wedd. (
<taxonomicName genus="Rosaceae" lsidName="Rosaceae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rosaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and produces conspicuous (3-14 cm in diam.) and black ascostromata. 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Shiraiaceae" genus="Shiraia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Shiraia" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shiraia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having muriform ascospores, however, it differs by its black and larger ascostromata. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirk, PM" journalOrPublisher="CABI, Wallingford" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Kirk, PM, Cannon, PF, Minter, DW, Stalpers, JA, 2008. Dictionary of the Fungi (10th edn). . CABI, Wallingford" title="Dictionary of the Fungi (10 th edn)." year="2008">Kirk et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3158/1557.1" author="Lumbsch, HT" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Life and Earth Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 64" refId="B37" refString="Lumbsch, HT, Huhndorf, SM, 2010. Myconet Volume 14. Part one. Outline of Ascomycota-2009. Part Two. Notes on Ascomycete Systematics. Nos. 4751-5113. . Fieldiana Life and Earth Sciences 1: 1 - 64" title="Myconet Volume 14. Part one. Outline of Ascomycota- 2009. Part Two. Notes on Ascomycete Systematics. Nos. 4751 - 5113." url="https://doi.org/10.3158/1557.1" volume="1" year="2010">Lumbsch and Huhndorf (2010)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="class">Dothideomycetes</taxonomicName>
, genera 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">incertae sedis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" author="Ariyawansa, HA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="35 - 47" refId="B2" refString="Ariyawansa, HA, Kang, JC, Alias, SA, Chukeatirote, E, Hyde, KD, 2013. Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis). . Phytotaxa 147: 35 - 47" title="Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" volume="147" year="2013">Ariyawansa et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
re-examined the type material and transferred it to 
<taxonomicName family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Pleosporales</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0309-2" author="Wijayawardene, NN" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 55" refId="B64" refString="Wijayawardene, NN, Crous, PW, Kirk, PM, Hawksworth, DL, Boonmee, S, Braun, U, Chomnunti, P, Dai, DQ, D'souza, MJ, Diederich, P, Dissanayake, A, Doilom, M, Hongsanan, S, Jones, EBG, Groenewald, JZ, Jayawardena, R, Lawrey, JD, Liu, JK, Luecking, R, Madrid, H, Manamgoda, DS, Muggia, L, Nelsen, MP, Phookamsak, R, Suetrong, S, Tanaka, K, Thambugala, KM, Wikee, S, Zhang, Y, Aptroot, A, Ariyawansa, HA, Bahkali, AH, Bhat, JD, Gueidan, C, De Hoog, GS, Knudsen, K, McKenzie, EHC, Miller, AN, Mortimer, PE, Wanasinghe, DN, Phillips, AJL, Raja, HA, Slippers, B, Shivas, RS, Taylor, JE, Wang, Y, Woudenberg, JHC, Piatek, M, Cai, L, Jaklitsch, WM, Hyde, KD, 2014. Naming and outline of Dothideomycetes. (2014) including proposals for the protection or suppression of generic names. . Fungal Diversity 69: 1 - 55" title="Naming and outline of Dothideomycetes. (2014) including proposals for the protection or suppression of generic names." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0309-2" volume="69" year="2014">Wijayawardene et al. (2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/8/7/9" author="Wijayawardene, NN" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="934 - 950" refId="B65" refString="Wijayawardene, NN, Papizadeh, M, Phillips, AJL, Wanasinghe, DN, Bhat, DJ, Weerahewa, HLD, Shenoy, BD, Wang, Y, Huang, YQ, 2017. Mycosphere Essays 19: Recent advances and future challenges in taxonomy of coelomycetous fungi. . Mycosphere 8: 934 - 950" title="Mycosphere Essays 19: Recent advances and future challenges in taxonomy of coelomycetous fungi." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/8/7/9" volume="8" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-018-0394-8" author="Wijayawardene, NN" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="167 - 263" refId="B66" refString="Wijayawardene, NN, Hyde, KD, Lumbsch, HT, Liu, JK, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Ekanayaka, AH, Tian, Q, Phookamsak, R, 2018. Outline of Ascomycota: 2017. . Fungal Diversity 88: 167 - 263" title="Outline of Ascomycota: 2017." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-018-0394-8" volume="88" year="2018">2018</bibRefCitation>
) accepted this placement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
